727715f-a.title: Queens: Queens Boulevard - Junction Boulevard
727715f-a.text:
Queens Boulevard (left), at the N.W. corner of Junction
Boulevard, showing Howard Johnson's Tavern. On the right is
Junction Boulevard, running north.
P. L. Sperr  July 1, 1940

725548f-a.title: Queens: 63rd Road - Queens Boulevard
725548f-a.text:
63rd Road, east from ueens Boulevard. Cn the left is the
H. Vancerveer house of 18bO. AuUhl owned it from 1873 to
1896. The house on the right was owned by the Vanderveers
from 1860 to 189o.
Augene L. Armbruster Collection  April, 1923

727813f-a.title: Queens: Queens Boulevard - 63rd Road
727813f-a.text:
Queens Boulevard, north side, just west of 63rd Road,
showing an old farmstead. It was owned by Eifert in 1891
and by one Uht in 1873.
P. L. Sperr  June 8, 1927
